1
00:00:01,330 --> 00:00:06,890
You don't want us to open the country either.

2
00:00:06,890 --> 00:00:08,530
Right?

3
00:00:09,980 --> 00:00:15,860
Because in order to fight pirates,
you buy weapons from pirates.

4
00:00:18,160 --> 00:00:21,220
Don't you find it strange?

5
00:00:21,220 --> 00:00:22,930
Hmm?!

6
00:00:26,890 --> 00:00:31,460
With your broker Doflamingo,
also known as Joker, out of the picture,

7
00:00:31,460 --> 00:00:39,180
you have no choice but
to trade with us directly.

8
00:00:39,180 --> 00:00:45,520
I know you're out on a limb,
so the advantage is mine...

9
00:00:47,390 --> 00:00:50,820
And already your demands are unreasonable.

10
00:00:50,820 --> 00:00:55,780
Look, Wano is entirely self-sufficient!

11
00:01:01,410 --> 00:01:05,540
Everyone here seems happy, right?

12
00:01:05,540 --> 00:01:10,170
If there is something we need,
that would be greater power!

13
00:01:10,170 --> 00:01:13,590
This time, I'm only asking for a warship...

14
00:01:14,970 --> 00:01:19,180
Next time, I'll want Dr. Vegapunk!

15
00:01:19,180 --> 00:01:21,010
That's impossible!

16
00:01:26,140 --> 00:01:29,730
I didn't ask if it's possible!

17
00:01:34,030 --> 00:01:37,590
The Celestial Dragons? The Marines?

18
00:01:37,590 --> 00:01:42,410
You know we're not afraid of them, right?

19
00:01:46,080 --> 00:01:50,290
You couldn't bring us down
even if you all banded together.

20
00:01:50,290 --> 00:01:54,840
I have Kaido backing me after all!

21
00:04:00,590 --> 00:04:05,390
Komurasaki the top oiran is in procession!

22
00:04:05,390 --> 00:04:08,420
Oh, Lady Komuraski!

23
00:04:08,420 --> 00:04:11,480
Look over here, Oiran!

24
00:04:18,210 --> 00:04:20,280
I'm sorry I'm late!

25
00:04:24,070 --> 00:04:26,120
I was worried about you.

26
00:04:27,490 --> 00:04:29,790
Please forgive me, Big Sis!

27
00:04:29,790 --> 00:04:31,930
Now, get to work.

28
00:04:32,650 --> 00:04:33,870
Okay!

29
00:04:39,590 --> 00:04:42,380
Here comes Lady Komurasaki!

30
00:04:45,180 --> 00:04:47,350
It's the oiran's procession!

31
00:04:48,690 --> 00:04:49,760
Isn't she here yet?!

32
00:04:49,760 --> 00:04:52,860
There're tons of people here.

33
00:04:52,860 --> 00:04:56,400
I wonder how beautiful she is!

34
00:04:56,400 --> 00:05:00,150
Please hurry, Komurasaki my beloved!

35
00:05:06,200 --> 00:05:09,080
That conniving tramp...

36
00:05:09,080 --> 00:05:11,160
...Komurasaki!

37
00:05:11,160 --> 00:05:12,580
Komurasaki!

38
00:05:12,920 --> 00:05:15,410
Komurasaki...!

39
00:05:17,460 --> 00:05:19,840
I think they're looking for trouble!

40
00:05:21,010 --> 00:05:22,370
H-Hey!

41
00:05:22,370 --> 00:05:23,840
I've got to...

42
00:05:23,840 --> 00:05:25,880
kill that bitch!

43
00:05:26,470 --> 00:05:29,260
I'll be driven out of the city...

44
00:05:29,270 --> 00:05:31,470
It's all over!

45
00:05:31,470 --> 00:05:34,220
If I'm gonna die,

46
00:05:34,220 --> 00:05:36,440
I'll take her with me!

47
00:05:46,350 --> 00:05:48,660
Stay away from the oiran!

48
00:06:01,670 --> 00:06:04,620
Komurasaki...

49
00:06:08,900 --> 00:06:13,560
I want to be with you forever, my love...

50
00:06:13,560 --> 00:06:14,450
What?

51
00:06:14,980 --> 00:06:17,890
W-With an old geezer like me?!

52
00:06:17,890 --> 00:06:22,580
If I have to live Shogun Orochi's puppet...

53
00:06:22,580 --> 00:06:26,860
I would rather you bought out my contract...

54
00:06:26,860 --> 00:06:30,910
Alas, the price for my freedom is so outrageous,

55
00:06:30,910 --> 00:06:33,870
it is an impossible dream...

56
00:06:33,870 --> 00:06:39,110
Imagine if Shogun Orochi were
to catch wind of this conversation.

57
00:06:40,010 --> 00:06:42,000
Don't fret, my dear!

58
00:06:42,740 --> 00:06:44,750
If that is your desire,

59
00:06:44,750 --> 00:06:48,550
I, Bingo, will make it happen!

60
00:06:50,700 --> 00:06:52,800
Really?

61
00:06:52,800 --> 00:06:56,980
I'm glad to hear it, even if you're not serious.

62
00:07:00,600 --> 00:07:02,990
You don't have enough money
to pay me back?!

63
00:07:02,990 --> 00:07:04,470
I'm sorry!

64
00:07:04,470 --> 00:07:07,110
Do you take me for a fool?!

65
00:07:07,780 --> 00:07:10,750
You think crying will help?!

66
00:07:10,750 --> 00:07:14,600
I'll take your house as collateral for the loan!

67
00:07:16,870 --> 00:07:19,210
Here, Komurasaki.

68
00:07:19,210 --> 00:07:22,900
I've never seen so much money!

69
00:07:22,900 --> 00:07:28,410
Komurasaki, here's an advance
to buy you from the pleasure hall.

70
00:07:28,410 --> 00:07:31,290
It's not enough yet,
but I want you to hold onto it.

71
00:07:31,290 --> 00:07:33,700
Then, let me enter it in the ledger.

72
00:07:33,700 --> 00:07:35,640
That's not necessary!

73
00:07:35,640 --> 00:07:39,350
Only a fool mistrusts the woman he loves.

74
00:07:39,350 --> 00:07:41,890
Your word is good enough for me.

75
00:07:41,890 --> 00:07:43,620
My lord Bingo...

76
00:07:44,690 --> 00:07:49,320
I cannot wait for the moment
you take me with you.

77
00:07:55,700 --> 00:07:57,900
Don't cry.

78
00:07:58,770 --> 00:07:59,750
It's all right!

79
00:07:59,750 --> 00:08:02,640
I'll make the funeral arrangements.

80
00:08:02,640 --> 00:08:06,220
I'll also lend you some money
for it and for living expenses.

81
00:08:09,210 --> 00:08:11,970
Stop crying already!

82
00:08:11,970 --> 00:08:14,940
You need to pay me back double!

83
00:08:14,940 --> 00:08:18,550
It's your own fault for being so naive!

84
00:08:20,840 --> 00:08:22,770
Here's your money!

85
00:08:22,770 --> 00:08:25,160
Wow! It's so much!

86
00:08:26,210 --> 00:08:27,400
But...

87
00:08:27,400 --> 00:08:29,090
What's wrong?

88
00:08:29,090 --> 00:08:34,430
The truth is, someone else recently
offered to buy my contract...

89
00:08:34,430 --> 00:08:35,660
What?!

90
00:08:35,660 --> 00:08:37,030
I have to hurry!

91
00:08:37,030 --> 00:08:42,040
I need more and more money to buy her...
Is there anything that I can sell?

92
00:08:44,210 --> 00:08:47,420
I sold my storehouse, Komurasaki!

93
00:08:47,420 --> 00:08:50,590
I'm so grateful...

94
00:08:50,590 --> 00:08:52,590
Enough is enough!

95
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:56,170
I'm fed up with you!

96
00:08:56,930 --> 00:09:00,000
I'm going back to my parents' house!

97
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:02,060
Do whatever you like!

98
00:09:04,290 --> 00:09:08,060
I'm on my way, Komurasaki!

99
00:09:10,560 --> 00:09:12,460
I've even abandoned my family!

100
00:09:14,610 --> 00:09:18,360
Oh no, you must think of your health...

101
00:09:19,300 --> 00:09:21,910
Medicine is a waste of money.

102
00:09:21,910 --> 00:09:24,010
I'll be fine.

103
00:09:24,010 --> 00:09:31,130
Once I get what I want,
I'll be the happiest man in the world.

104
00:09:31,130 --> 00:09:38,340
I admit that I dream of my life
with you every single night...

105
00:09:38,340 --> 00:09:42,190
Oh... Komurasaki!

106
00:09:47,310 --> 00:09:48,860
I got the last of it...

107
00:09:48,860 --> 00:09:54,240
I may not have a house, but we'll be
free to start our new life together!

108
00:09:54,240 --> 00:09:57,240
I have the final 500 gold.

109
00:09:57,240 --> 00:10:02,240
With this, I can buy your
contract, Komurasaki!

110
00:10:04,200 --> 00:10:05,450
Huh?

111
00:10:05,450 --> 00:10:09,630
I'm sorry. The oiran is sick today...

112
00:10:09,630 --> 00:10:11,340
Oh no!

113
00:10:12,070 --> 00:10:16,460
Just be sure to give her this. I'll be back later...

114
00:10:22,280 --> 00:10:24,560
Komurasaki!

115
00:10:24,560 --> 00:10:31,430
I've come to liberate you from
the pleasure hall! Come live with me!

116
00:10:42,990 --> 00:10:45,460
You really fell for it!

117
00:10:45,460 --> 00:10:48,620
Way to go, you old pervert!

118
00:10:49,610 --> 00:10:52,210
Hey, guys!

119
00:10:52,210 --> 00:10:56,810
Quit laughing and get Komurasaki for me.

120
00:10:58,900 --> 00:11:03,100
She's going to live happily ever after with me!

121
00:11:05,600 --> 00:11:08,940
You moron! Dream on!

122
00:11:08,940 --> 00:11:11,100
You have enough money to liberate her?

123
00:11:11,100 --> 00:11:15,730
Of course I do! Komurasaki already has it!
I asked her to keep it safe for me!

124
00:11:17,700 --> 00:11:20,150
Oh my... It's Mr. Bingo.

125
00:11:20,150 --> 00:11:24,670
Oh, Komurasaki! Please set things straight!

126
00:11:24,670 --> 00:11:30,240
They're running their mouths, completely
unaware of our devotion to one another!

127
00:11:30,240 --> 00:11:31,600
Oh?

128
00:11:33,000 --> 00:11:37,670
You gave me that money, did you not?

129
00:11:38,390 --> 00:11:39,220
What?!

130
00:11:45,830 --> 00:11:48,970
I've already spent it all.

131
00:11:50,010 --> 00:11:51,560
But thank you.

132
00:11:53,790 --> 00:11:59,320
This old coot really thought
Komurasaki was in love with him!

133
00:12:12,700 --> 00:12:15,880
What's with the old fart?

134
00:12:15,880 --> 00:12:16,710
What?

135
00:12:16,710 --> 00:12:18,670
Komurasaki...

136
00:12:20,670 --> 00:12:23,340
B-Boss Kyoshiro!

137
00:12:24,200 --> 00:12:25,720
So...

138
00:12:25,720 --> 00:12:30,850
you're the old man who's been hanging
around Komurasaki these days...

139
00:12:30,850 --> 00:12:34,400
Hanging around...? L-Let me explain!

140
00:12:34,400 --> 00:12:37,980
Komurasaki, this is a joke, right?

141
00:12:40,570 --> 00:12:44,500
I really did sacrifice all I had!

142
00:12:44,500 --> 00:12:46,740
I don't have anything left!

143
00:12:46,740 --> 00:12:50,660
I gave it all up for you!

144
00:13:01,100 --> 00:13:02,920
Well then...

145
00:13:02,920 --> 00:13:05,210
How many of these saps has it been now?

146
00:13:05,210 --> 00:13:09,500
We can't have you crying out here
and obstructing business, old man.

147
00:13:09,500 --> 00:13:13,180
If you're done, beat it!

148
00:13:13,890 --> 00:13:16,520
You lecherous old geezer!

149
00:13:22,360 --> 00:13:24,860
Stop!

150
00:13:24,860 --> 00:13:26,860
Stop...!

151
00:13:27,780 --> 00:13:29,780
I'm leaving!

152
00:13:29,780 --> 00:13:33,200
I'm leaving, so just stop!

153
00:13:45,000 --> 00:13:46,930
Komurasaki...!

154
00:13:54,400 --> 00:13:57,600
Komurasaki the top oiran...

155
00:14:00,400 --> 00:14:03,930
is in procession!

156
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:10,830
– Lady Komurasaki!
– Lady Komurasaki!

157
00:14:15,480 --> 00:14:17,330
She's stunning!

158
00:14:17,330 --> 00:14:19,710
She's gorgeous!

159
00:14:24,460 --> 00:14:26,890
Oh, she's beautiful...!

160
00:14:26,890 --> 00:14:29,470
She's radiant! My eyes!

161
00:14:33,510 --> 00:14:35,390
Komurasaki!

162
00:14:35,390 --> 00:14:38,600
I sold my house, my family,
and everything else!

163
00:14:38,600 --> 00:14:43,800
Give me back my money, you thief!

164
00:14:45,400 --> 00:14:48,070
Asking for your gift back?

165
00:14:48,750 --> 00:14:51,690
What a pathetic display...

166
00:14:52,370 --> 00:14:57,500
To me, men are just dogs
who fetch me money.

167
00:14:57,500 --> 00:15:00,330
If you can't do that anymore,
you're dead to me.

168
00:15:05,000 --> 00:15:07,510
Gentlemen, that's as far as you go!

169
00:15:08,810 --> 00:15:11,510
If your wallets are empty, then get lost!

170
00:15:11,510 --> 00:15:15,720
Anyone who can't generate wealth
has no place in the Flower Capital.

171
00:15:15,720 --> 00:15:20,270
In the name of Shogun Orochi,
we'll expel you from the city!

172
00:15:23,390 --> 00:15:25,400
Please don't!

173
00:15:25,400 --> 00:15:29,400
The conditions outside the city are inhumane!

174
00:15:29,400 --> 00:15:31,990
Damn! Go to hell!

175
00:15:31,990 --> 00:15:35,130
Komurasaki!

176
00:15:36,100 --> 00:15:40,410
I have nothing but scorn...

177
00:15:40,410 --> 00:15:43,080
for the poor.

178
00:16:00,350 --> 00:16:03,170
Open the gate!

179
00:16:11,120 --> 00:16:15,740
Komurasaki the top oiran has arrived!

180
00:16:33,880 --> 00:16:36,810
So you have a little sister, Momo?

181
00:16:36,810 --> 00:16:38,010
Hey, Tama!

182
00:16:38,010 --> 00:16:41,430
It is rude to address me so casually!
Who do you think I am?!

183
00:16:41,430 --> 00:16:42,940
You're Momo.

184
00:16:43,940 --> 00:16:45,060
Forget it.

185
00:16:46,650 --> 00:16:49,390
Yes, I have a little sister.

186
00:16:49,390 --> 00:16:51,530
If she is alive, she would be twenty-six.

187
00:16:52,410 --> 00:16:57,990
There were witnesses to my mother's death,
but no one has confirmed whether Hiyori died.

188
00:16:57,990 --> 00:17:02,830
So I have faith that she is still out there!

189
00:17:02,830 --> 00:17:05,170
I hope you get to see her again.

190
00:17:05,170 --> 00:17:07,080
Well, I won't!

191
00:17:07,080 --> 00:17:11,510
If her identity were to be exposed,
Orochi would target her!

192
00:17:12,400 --> 00:17:15,570
We will reunite only when the battle is won!

193
00:17:21,640 --> 00:17:26,460
You think you can show up late to work
because of some gorgeous oiran, Franko?!

194
00:17:26,460 --> 00:17:27,940
No, Boss!

195
00:17:27,940 --> 00:17:29,770
I'm so sorry!

196
00:17:30,700 --> 00:17:34,070
I mean, it's hard to believe
such a beauty exists!

197
00:17:35,920 --> 00:17:39,050
I know how you feel!

198
00:17:42,840 --> 00:17:47,500
But you know I have my
reputation to uphold, you dolt!

199
00:17:50,250 --> 00:17:53,010
Yes! I'm so sorry!

200
00:17:53,010 --> 00:17:59,470
I had no intention of bringing dishonor to the name
of Minatomo, the legendary master carpenter!

201
00:18:00,100 --> 00:18:03,310
Since you put in ten times the amount
of work than anyone else,

202
00:18:03,310 --> 00:18:06,330
I guess I don't mind if you
ditch work sometimes.

203
00:18:06,330 --> 00:18:11,860
If you show me the plans of
the Onigashima stronghold you built,

204
00:18:11,860 --> 00:18:12,900
I'll put in ten–

205
00:18:12,900 --> 00:18:17,070
No! A hundred times the amount of work!

206
00:18:17,990 --> 00:18:19,630
Oh, yeah.

207
00:18:19,630 --> 00:18:26,160
About those Onigashima mansion blueprints
you keep asking me about...

208
00:18:26,160 --> 00:18:29,120
About those... Um...

209
00:18:33,500 --> 00:18:36,470
Oh, this is just a tissue.

210
00:18:37,500 --> 00:18:38,630
Oh, come on!

211
00:18:41,090 --> 00:18:42,350
About those...

212
00:18:46,680 --> 00:18:48,440
I just remembered...

213
00:18:50,890 --> 00:18:54,320
I pawned them about ten years ago!

214
00:19:08,590 --> 00:19:14,170
Why the hell do you think I've been
working for you for all these weeks?!

215
00:19:14,170 --> 00:19:17,630
Ouch! Damn it, cut it out, Franko!

216
00:19:21,550 --> 00:19:25,180
You attacked your master!
Who do you think you are?!

217
00:19:25,180 --> 00:19:27,310
You blockhead!

218
00:19:27,310 --> 00:19:29,480
You're driving me crazy!

219
00:19:31,230 --> 00:19:32,270
Eat this!

220
00:19:32,270 --> 00:19:35,480
Franosuke Rocket Launcher!

221
00:19:40,780 --> 00:19:43,870
You're fired! Get out of here, you simpleton!

222
00:19:43,870 --> 00:19:46,490
Gladly! I no longer have
business here anyway!

223
00:19:49,210 --> 00:19:52,790
Blueprints pawned ten years ago?

224
00:19:53,510 --> 00:19:56,670
It's rare that we would ever take those...

225
00:19:58,990 --> 00:20:00,380
Oh, maybe those!

226
00:20:00,380 --> 00:20:02,720
What? Do you have them?!

227
00:20:02,720 --> 00:20:07,070
Well, of course, they've long since
gone to somebody else...

228
00:20:07,070 --> 00:20:09,770
Now, who would've bought such an item...?

229
00:20:09,770 --> 00:20:12,890
Hmm, who was it...?

230
00:20:12,890 --> 00:20:15,610
Um...

231
00:20:16,420 --> 00:20:17,690
Oh, yeah!

232
00:20:18,340 --> 00:20:22,700
It was Kumagoro from the tenements.
He said he'd study them. No doubt about it!

233
00:20:24,000 --> 00:20:25,160
Who?!

234
00:20:25,160 --> 00:20:25,200
Who?!

235
00:20:25,200 --> 00:20:25,240
Who?!

236
00:20:25,240 --> 00:20:25,280
Who?!

237
00:20:26,100 --> 00:20:28,790
Kumagoro!

238
00:20:28,790 --> 00:20:30,790
Blueprints?

239
00:20:30,790 --> 00:20:34,100
Oh yeah, I had them at one point,

240
00:20:34,100 --> 00:20:38,550
but I fell behind on my rent,
so my landlord Mr. Kobe took them.

241
00:20:39,590 --> 00:20:41,470
Who the hell is that?

242
00:20:41,470 --> 00:20:41,510
Who the hell is that?

243
00:20:41,510 --> 00:20:41,550
Who the hell is that?

244
00:20:41,550 --> 00:20:41,590
Who the hell is that?

245
00:20:41,590 --> 00:20:41,630
Who the hell is that?

246
00:20:42,420 --> 00:20:44,130
Kobe!

247
00:20:44,130 --> 00:20:49,990
Oh, the blueprints. They were of high quality,
so I gave them to my favorite geisha.

248
00:20:49,990 --> 00:20:50,970
Miss Kisegawa.

249
00:20:50,970 --> 00:20:52,400
Do you know her?

250
00:20:52,400 --> 00:20:53,480
No!

251
00:20:53,480 --> 00:20:53,520
No!

252
00:20:53,520 --> 00:20:53,560
No!

253
00:20:53,560 --> 00:20:53,600
No!

254
00:20:53,600 --> 00:20:53,640
No!

255
00:20:54,480 --> 00:20:59,230
I didn't know what to do with them, so I used
them as a dish mat, but then Tokijiro...

256
00:20:59,230 --> 00:21:01,490
Okay, and who is that?

257
00:21:01,490 --> 00:21:01,530
Okay, and who is that?

258
00:21:01,530 --> 00:21:01,570
Okay, and who is that?

259
00:21:01,860 --> 00:21:01,900
I had them!

260
00:21:01,900 --> 00:21:01,940
I had them!

261
00:21:01,940 --> 00:21:03,780
I had them!

262
00:21:03,780 --> 00:21:06,990
But the Camel said they could fetch
a high price and took them!

263
00:21:06,990 --> 00:21:09,700
What? "The Camel"?! An animal did?!

264
00:21:09,700 --> 00:21:09,740
What? "The Camel"?! An animal did?!

265
00:21:09,740 --> 00:21:09,790
What? "The Camel"?! An animal did?!

266
00:21:09,790 --> 00:21:09,830
What? "The Camel"?! An animal did?!

267
00:21:09,830 --> 00:21:09,870
What? "The Camel"?! An animal did?!

268
00:21:09,870 --> 00:21:09,910
What? "The Camel"?! An animal did?!

269
00:21:09,910 --> 00:21:09,950
What? "The Camel"?! An animal did?!

270
00:21:09,950 --> 00:21:09,990
What? "The Camel"?! An animal did?!

271
00:21:09,990 --> 00:21:10,040
What? "The Camel"?! An animal did?!

272
00:21:10,040 --> 00:21:10,080
What? "The Camel"?! An animal did?!

273
00:21:10,810 --> 00:21:12,770
They call me the Camel!

274
00:21:12,770 --> 00:21:16,230
Man, those blueprints
gave me nothing but trouble!

275
00:21:16,230 --> 00:21:18,290
Some guy made off with them!

276
00:21:18,290 --> 00:21:23,550
His face was covered,
but he said he came from Kuri.

277
00:21:23,550 --> 00:21:26,100
Kuri?!

278
00:21:30,310 --> 00:21:30,930
Um...

279
00:21:30,930 --> 00:21:34,000
Oh, I'm sorry. It's sea bream.

280
00:21:34,000 --> 00:21:36,230
Is that how sea bream usually looks?

281
00:21:36,230 --> 00:21:39,110
Nice doing business with you!

282
00:21:43,030 --> 00:21:44,490
Sir Franosuke!

283
00:21:46,400 --> 00:21:48,240
You seem to be in high spirits.

284
00:21:48,240 --> 00:21:51,370
Of course! But what in
the world are you selling?

285
00:21:51,370 --> 00:21:55,090
What? Oh, I'm peddling fish.

286
00:21:55,090 --> 00:21:58,790
You stick out like a sore thumb!
Kids are drawn to you!

287
00:21:58,790 --> 00:22:04,910
Anyway, why were you in such a hurry?
Is anything the matter?

288
00:22:04,910 --> 00:22:10,350
Oh, yeah! Forget sticking out!
We've got bigger fish to fry!

289
00:22:10,350 --> 00:22:16,060
The guy I thought had the blueprints
didn't have them after all!

290
00:22:17,550 --> 00:22:20,560
Check the swords over there next.

291
00:22:20,560 --> 00:22:25,740
What?! The blueprints for Kaido's
mansion are here in Kuri?!

292
00:22:25,740 --> 00:22:30,450
Yeah! I couldn't find them even after
running all over the capital!

293
00:22:30,450 --> 00:22:33,150
I'm not sure what I should do now!

294
00:22:34,210 --> 00:22:36,660
I'm sorry you had to go through that.

295
00:22:36,660 --> 00:22:40,750
Sir Franosuke, please help the others
complete their missions in the capital.

296
00:22:40,750 --> 00:22:42,390
Got it!

297
00:22:43,600 --> 00:22:48,520
Hmm... Who would want
the blueprints of Kaido's mansion?

298
00:22:48,520 --> 00:22:49,910
Could it be...?

299
00:22:50,800 --> 00:22:52,720
Your Grace! Sir Kin!

300
00:22:52,720 --> 00:22:54,770
Hey!

301
00:22:55,470 --> 00:22:56,770
Whew!

302
00:22:56,770 --> 00:23:01,940
Look at all we stole! There's food
and weapons from the factory!

303
00:23:01,940 --> 00:23:05,150
Nice work. Did you leave the calling card?

304
00:23:05,150 --> 00:23:06,780
We sure did!

305
00:23:08,650 --> 00:23:10,550
But should we have?

306
00:23:10,550 --> 00:23:16,200
The note might cause the Beast Pirates
to attack Ashura Doji.

307
00:23:16,200 --> 00:23:20,580
That is what we want.
Coming under attack will infuriate him.

308
00:23:20,580 --> 00:23:25,420
If we don't use his rage to goad him
into fighting the Beast Pirates...

309
00:23:25,420 --> 00:23:28,680
we'll never rekindle the fire within him.

310
00:23:31,690 --> 00:23:38,210
Considering the regret he's suffered for
twenty years, this seems a bit heavy-handed.

311
00:23:38,210 --> 00:23:39,600
I know!

312
00:23:39,600 --> 00:23:45,230
But whether the means be fair or foul,
we need him if we are to topple Kaido!

313
00:23:45,900 --> 00:23:48,690
We need Ashura Doji's help!

314
00:23:51,400 --> 00:23:54,870
Hey! I'm back!

315
00:24:00,410 --> 00:24:01,790
Yasu!

316
00:24:02,790 --> 00:24:05,960
Oh, you're back, Tonoyasu!

317
00:24:05,960 --> 00:24:09,590
Yasu, you're back, but we
still don't have any food!

318
00:24:11,080 --> 00:24:12,760
I'm so hungry!

319
00:24:13,690 --> 00:24:15,550
I'm starving to death!

320
00:24:24,800 --> 00:24:27,400
How come they're so cheerful?

321
00:24:27,400 --> 00:24:28,860
Wow!

322
00:24:28,860 --> 00:24:33,200
You're quick on the uptake, mister!
Everyone here looks happy, right?!

323
00:24:33,940 --> 00:24:36,660
It's slightly different from
Okobore Town in Kuri.

324
00:24:39,070 --> 00:24:43,790
Amongst all the species,
only humans can laugh!

325
00:24:43,790 --> 00:24:44,670
Yeah!

326
00:24:44,670 --> 00:24:48,900
♪ That's why you just gotta laugh! ♪

327
00:24:50,680 --> 00:24:52,760
♪ You just gotta laugh! ♪

328
00:24:54,970 --> 00:24:57,280
♪ You just gotta laugh! ♪

329
00:25:00,720 --> 00:25:02,680
Pardon us!

330
00:25:11,590 --> 00:25:12,990
– Shogun Orochi!
– Shogun Orochi!

331
00:25:21,200 --> 00:25:25,120
Don't be reserved! Raise your heads!

332
00:25:26,330 --> 00:25:30,090
Now, what's for dinner?

333
00:25:30,090 --> 00:25:33,380
Yes! Everything is ready!

334
00:25:33,380 --> 00:25:34,620
Bring it in!

335
00:25:37,340 --> 00:25:39,220
Oh!

336
00:25:39,220 --> 00:25:43,400
We slaughtered the chickens we bred in
the beautiful environs of Orochi Farm,

337
00:25:43,400 --> 00:25:45,060
then parboiled them...

338
00:25:45,060 --> 00:25:47,060
No! I don't feel like chicken!

339
00:25:47,060 --> 00:25:49,600
Yes, my lord! We'll discard them!

340
00:25:49,600 --> 00:25:51,100
Take it away!

341
00:25:51,100 --> 00:25:52,150
Next!

342
00:25:52,150 --> 00:25:54,450
These fresh, delicious vegetables...

343
00:25:54,450 --> 00:25:55,370
I don't want them!

344
00:25:55,370 --> 00:25:57,280
Yes, my lord! We'll throw them out!

345
00:25:57,280 --> 00:25:58,360
Next!

346
00:25:59,390 --> 00:26:02,450
We present some of the finest,
fattiest saury available!

347
00:26:03,620 --> 00:26:06,100
I like saury!

348
00:26:06,100 --> 00:26:07,900
And tuna sashimi!

349
00:26:07,910 --> 00:26:10,790
Yeah! Nothing beats tuna! Tuna!

350
00:26:10,790 --> 00:26:14,880
And we have selected a variety
of sake from across Wano...

351
00:26:14,880 --> 00:26:16,840
I get it!

352
00:26:18,410 --> 00:26:21,730
Of course you have plenty
of sake to go around!

353
00:26:21,730 --> 00:26:24,120
But how about women?

354
00:26:24,120 --> 00:26:25,770
Of course, right away!

355
00:26:25,770 --> 00:26:27,890
Good! Good!

356
00:26:33,980 --> 00:26:36,920
Mom, I'm hungry!

357
00:26:36,920 --> 00:26:38,780
Me, too!

358
00:26:41,570 --> 00:26:45,450
My tooth fell out from malnutrition!

359
00:26:46,900 --> 00:26:49,280
Not like you have any food to chew anyway!

360
00:26:51,170 --> 00:26:54,960
Now, Tonoyasu, who is this ronin fellow?

361
00:26:54,960 --> 00:26:57,760
He has three swords belted on!

362
00:26:58,760 --> 00:27:01,580
You're right! Three swords!

363
00:27:01,580 --> 00:27:03,260
And they're all long swords!

364
00:27:03,260 --> 00:27:05,100
Are you trying to be funny?!

365
00:27:07,090 --> 00:27:11,790
Whoa, whoa! I admire this gentleman!

366
00:27:11,790 --> 00:27:16,400
Oh no! I'm sorry to hear you've had
this weirdo following you around.

367
00:27:16,400 --> 00:27:19,820
Wrong! I'm the world's greatest sycophant!

368
00:27:19,820 --> 00:27:22,020
Right, handsome?!

369
00:27:23,000 --> 00:27:27,500
He sure is, but look!
He has that frightful expression!

370
00:27:27,500 --> 00:27:31,830
Come on, young man. Drop the scary look.

371
00:27:34,300 --> 00:27:36,710
Give us a smile!

372
00:27:36,710 --> 00:27:40,300
Good things happen, even in
a miserable hole like Ebisu!

373
00:27:40,300 --> 00:27:44,970
Wait, are you saying he
paid this town a visit?!

374
00:27:44,970 --> 00:27:49,930
That's right! The Witching Hour Boy
paid us another visit!

375
00:27:51,520 --> 00:27:53,310
That's great!

376
00:27:53,310 --> 00:27:55,480
Witching-whozit?

377
00:27:55,480 --> 00:27:59,400
Yeah, he always comes by
when we're in trouble!

378
00:27:59,400 --> 00:28:02,830
We don't even know who he is.

379
00:28:04,120 --> 00:28:07,900
He appears at the witching hour

380
00:28:07,900 --> 00:28:11,460
and steals money from the rich,
evil people of the capital...

381
00:28:19,400 --> 00:28:23,690
He leaves the money at
poor tenements and disappears.

382
00:28:23,690 --> 00:28:26,630
I wonder who he is.

383
00:28:26,630 --> 00:28:29,510
Thank goodness, thank goodness!

384
00:28:30,600 --> 00:28:32,940
Fortune comes to those who laugh!

385
00:28:32,940 --> 00:28:37,160
So we pooled our money to ourselves a treat!

386
00:28:38,320 --> 00:28:41,150
Oh! What kind of treat?!

387
00:28:41,150 --> 00:28:43,130
Here it is!

388
00:28:43,130 --> 00:28:44,410
You see?

389
00:28:44,410 --> 00:28:46,280
This is it!

390
00:28:47,190 --> 00:28:49,120
Please have a cup!

391
00:28:50,850 --> 00:28:52,460
You should have some, too!

392
00:28:54,190 --> 00:28:56,000
It's clear water!

393
00:28:56,000 --> 00:28:58,340
We bought it with the money we were given!

394
00:29:01,840 --> 00:29:04,050
No, I shouldn't...

395
00:29:04,050 --> 00:29:05,730
Don't worry!

396
00:29:06,890 --> 00:29:11,390
This water's clean, so you
won't get a tummy ache!

397
00:29:11,390 --> 00:29:16,090
Yasu brought you here,
so you must be a good man!

398
00:29:20,520 --> 00:29:22,800
Don't be shy!

399
00:29:22,800 --> 00:29:27,620
Go ahead and drink! Everyone
has the right to have some!

400
00:29:27,620 --> 00:29:29,740
♪ Delicious water! ♪

401
00:29:29,740 --> 00:29:31,740
♪ Clear water! ♪

402
00:29:31,740 --> 00:29:34,080
♪ Delicious water! ♪

403
00:29:34,080 --> 00:29:36,210
♪ Clear water! ♪

404
00:29:36,210 --> 00:29:40,630
♪ Delicious water! Clear water! ♪

405
00:29:40,630 --> 00:29:44,680
♪ Delicious water! Clear water! ♪

406
00:29:44,680 --> 00:29:49,340
♪ Delicious water! Clear water! ♪

407
00:30:02,030 --> 00:30:04,940
Good huh?! It seeps into every
fiber of your being, right?!

408
00:30:05,780 --> 00:30:08,530
There's that scary look again!

409
00:30:10,950 --> 00:30:14,090
Smile, or fortune won't smile on you!

410
00:30:14,790 --> 00:30:18,420
In this country, we call
everyone's smiling face

411
00:30:18,420 --> 00:30:22,420
an Ebisu grin, mister!

412
00:30:22,420 --> 00:30:25,450
That's why this place is called Ebisu!

413
00:30:25,450 --> 00:30:28,550
We won't let poverty get us down!

414
00:30:28,550 --> 00:30:32,560
♪ Crying won't cure your poverty! ♪
♪ So, you just gotta laugh! ♪

415
00:30:32,560 --> 00:30:35,060
♪ You just gotta laugh! ♪

416
00:30:42,020 --> 00:30:45,240
Enough waiting! Let me see them!

417
00:30:45,240 --> 00:30:47,490
Just a moment, my lord!

418
00:30:48,740 --> 00:30:53,240
Oh, yeah! These girls are fabulous! Fabulous!

419
00:30:57,830 --> 00:31:01,990
A-Are you pleased with them, my lord?

420
00:31:01,990 --> 00:31:04,880
They're... gorgeous!

421
00:31:06,200 --> 00:31:10,430
Simply superb! Let's start
the banquet immediately!

422
00:31:10,430 --> 00:31:11,680
Drink!

423
00:31:11,680 --> 00:31:13,300
Dance!

424
00:31:13,300 --> 00:31:15,140
Sing!

425
00:31:15,140 --> 00:31:18,050
Don't hold back!

426
00:31:27,400 --> 00:31:29,400
I have arrived, my lord...

427
00:31:39,000 --> 00:31:42,790
Oh, Komurasaki! I've missed you!

428
00:31:44,110 --> 00:31:46,340
And I, you...

429
00:31:47,100 --> 00:31:48,010
my lord.

430
00:31:48,010 --> 00:31:50,430
Oh, y-you did?!

431
00:31:53,640 --> 00:31:55,540
You did?!

432
00:32:04,590 --> 00:32:07,440
Traf, what brings you here?

433
00:32:07,440 --> 00:32:11,490
We have an emergency.
You need to hide, Black Leg.

434
00:32:12,410 --> 00:32:16,200
This about the fight earlier? If they
come back, I'll just beat them again.

435
00:32:16,200 --> 00:32:17,660
That's not it.

436
00:32:18,500 --> 00:32:21,080
The guys that are coming know our faces!

437
00:32:22,990 --> 00:32:24,000
Is it Hawkins?

438
00:32:24,000 --> 00:32:27,590
It wouldn't be so bad if it was just him...

439
00:32:28,500 --> 00:32:32,600
The six strongest headliners
are known as the Soaring Six.

440
00:32:33,390 --> 00:32:34,890
Two of them are coming here.

441
00:32:34,890 --> 00:32:36,050
Two?

442
00:32:36,050 --> 00:32:40,270
The first is Page One from the Soaring Six.

443
00:32:49,480 --> 00:32:52,650
The Soaring Six... Page One...

444
00:32:52,650 --> 00:32:57,830
The other one is X Drake from the Soaring Six.

445
00:32:57,830 --> 00:32:59,900
Drake...

446
00:32:59,900 --> 00:33:02,540
He's from the Worst Generation...

447
00:33:06,800 --> 00:33:12,050
Page One, why do we have to do this?

448
00:33:17,430 --> 00:33:19,500
To set an example, I guess...

449
00:33:19,500 --> 00:33:28,340
We've got to show them what happens
when you cross the Beast Pirates in Wano.

450
00:33:28,340 --> 00:33:31,030
So, why are you here...

451
00:33:31,530 --> 00:33:32,810
Hawkins?

452
00:33:32,810 --> 00:33:35,460
I'm looking for someone.

453
00:33:35,460 --> 00:33:40,280
You'll get more than you
bargained for with this job, Drake...

454
00:33:48,540 --> 00:33:53,840
Have you thought about
my offer from earlier, Boss?

455
00:33:53,840 --> 00:33:58,620
If you're gonna break out,
take me with you!

456
00:33:58,620 --> 00:34:00,930
I'll do anything!

457
00:34:00,930 --> 00:34:05,770
If we join forces, we'll be unstoppable!

458
00:34:05,770 --> 00:34:09,540
Shut up already! Why don't
you team up with Jaggy?!

459
00:34:09,540 --> 00:34:11,070
You mean Kid?

460
00:34:11,070 --> 00:34:15,660
No way. His reputation is terrible.

461
00:34:15,660 --> 00:34:21,870
Did you hear he tried to take down Big Mom?!

462
00:34:21,870 --> 00:34:27,110
Rumor has it one of her subordinates—
not her—took his arm,

463
00:34:27,110 --> 00:34:29,840
after which he escaped!

464
00:34:30,880 --> 00:34:34,720
Rumor? It's pathetic to listen
to that kinda crap.

465
00:34:34,970 --> 00:34:41,220
Nah, I heard it from a trusted source, Boss.

466
00:34:44,480 --> 00:34:47,940
Who is this source?

467
00:34:47,940 --> 00:34:52,360
I've never tried to take down Big Mom!

468
00:34:52,360 --> 00:34:55,100
K-K-K-Kid!

469
00:34:55,100 --> 00:34:58,000
I wounded one of her Sweet Commanders,

470
00:34:58,000 --> 00:35:00,700
took what I wanted, and left!

471
00:35:00,700 --> 00:35:03,240
B-B-B-But your arm...

472
00:35:03,240 --> 00:35:09,580
I'd already lost it before that,
in a battle against the Red Hair Pirates.

473
00:35:12,300 --> 00:35:14,150
Any other questions?!

474
00:35:14,150 --> 00:35:14,880
None.

475
00:35:14,880 --> 00:35:20,380
Then, let me tell you something!
You listen up, too, you stupid monkey!

476
00:35:20,380 --> 00:35:21,340
What?!

477
00:35:22,010 --> 00:35:25,900
I'm the one who's gonna take down
Kaido and get the glory!

478
00:35:25,900 --> 00:35:27,880
No, I am!

479
00:35:27,880 --> 00:35:28,770
What?!

480
00:35:38,570 --> 00:35:42,700
Everyone, the Fire Festival is nearly upon us!

481
00:35:42,700 --> 00:35:45,030
Let's consider this party the opening act!

482
00:35:45,030 --> 00:35:48,410
Go ahead and indulge yourselves!

483
00:35:48,410 --> 00:35:51,920
This is Wano!

484
00:35:51,920 --> 00:35:54,340
We may as well be in heaven!

485
00:35:54,340 --> 00:35:57,710
Eat and drink to your heart's content!

486
00:36:06,040 --> 00:36:10,350
They're approaching from
the southeast in a massive ship!

487
00:36:12,020 --> 00:36:14,520
She actually came!

488
00:36:15,200 --> 00:36:17,070
Blast them!

489
00:36:17,070 --> 00:36:19,920
Don't let her enter the country!

490
00:36:19,920 --> 00:36:23,910
But there is a problem...

491
00:36:30,080 --> 00:36:34,920
Carp are pulling their ship
and they're charing ahead!

492
00:36:34,920 --> 00:36:36,600
What?!

493
00:36:36,600 --> 00:36:40,090
How do they know how
to climb the waterfall?!

494
00:36:40,090 --> 00:36:46,180
Well, the Big Mom Pirates are
known for gathering good intel.

495
00:36:46,180 --> 00:36:49,100
Shut it! I don't care!

496
00:36:49,100 --> 00:36:51,890
We knew they were coming!

497
00:36:51,890 --> 00:36:54,190
Just sink them already!

498
00:37:00,200 --> 00:37:07,620
That old bag! I'm sure she
remembers that I warned her...

499
00:37:07,620 --> 00:37:12,830
I'll kill you if you come here, Linlin!

500
00:38:46,890 --> 00:38:50,870
I won't let you get away, Straw Hat...

